play.comments:
Played my first solo game wrong (gave Rugwort a card after every *action* rather than when I actually played a card!) so this was far more manageable!

Focussed on special goals and managed to get two finished by the end!

Rugwort: 35
Me: 47
Difference (for stats): 12 #bgstats

Absolutely whooped by Naomi (her first 2p win) as she managed to snag the Lieutenant in an early round and steamrollered ahead. My failed attempts to bag extra points through intreague and buildings only seemed to help her! The highest score I've seen ever... very nicely played.... dammit! #bgstats
Our first mega-game using all our tiles available (approx 300) #bgstats
Lucy survived two attacks - M.V.V. (Most Valuable Villager) again! #bgstats

Lucy died! We had a hard time with items on monster cards - drew all the "0 item" cards early so struggled with getting enough for all the monsters. We were down to the last monster card with Creature and if his attack roll had been a special (!) then we absolutely would have lost. A very narrow victory! #bgstats
Finished with 7 rounds to spare - what a team! #bgstats
I lost 78 points due to poverty. Went up to 110 points before unpaid loans and 31 excess poverty tokens pretty much took me out #bgstats

All came down to the final turn. Matt (Shark) got all 9 swimmers in Act 1, finishing with Michael Brody for double swimmer treats.
In Act 2 the Shark took out most of the boat but a few badly planned resurfaces meant that the crew got multiple attacks and killed me!
A few awkward rules and some of the actions felt a little clunky, but enjoyable and we will try again with reversed roles soon! #bgstats
Decided by tiebreak. Naomi had the most events (and would have had most leftover resources anyway!) #bgstats

4 - Crypt of the Damned

What we hoped would be a "quick, easy scenario" turned out to be a grind of cultists summoning enemies left, right and centre.

Some fantastic moves from Cragheart and Brute, but the Spellweaver was on the point of death from the first opened door and my Tinkerer felt underwhelming until the end.

We split in the corridor and I managed to lay enough traps to finish the last enemy with my final card - a single bad modifier would have lost us the game.

After that, the Brute was forced to retire, so our party now has the Human Sawbones (Oliver) who sounds... interesting ? #bgstats

11 - Gloomhaven Square A

Our tactic of running like a mad bastard worked well. Let the living bones and corpses tank the damage behind us.

Ended up knocking out the big boss in a couple of turns, once we got to him.

Strangely easy - and now the militaristic rule of Gloomhaven is toppled! #bgstats

We did the beginner game and smashed them both quickly.

With the legend that is Lucy holding back BOTH Drac and Creach for a couple of turns, she earned the MVP.

The Slag. #bgstats

We got hammered right from the start.

Had hardly made any progress with the monsters (less than 50% advanced) before we got beat.

Three monsters - especially these three - was a tricky game ? #bgstats

Had to be a lot more strategic about investment tokens with so many big build actions. 

Managed to win with 2 rounds spare ? #bgstats

Airport Easy is 11 rounds plus Seaport (+10 rounds) to start the timer at 21.

Tried a couple of the expansion modules for a longer game this evening. Really getting the swing of things now and know a couple of tricks to manage my investment tokens better.

Focused on challenge card first (which did seem the easiest of the bunch) and then onto the Seaport contracts (from bottom to top as well!).

Won on the second to last round with tokens and resources to spare! #bgstats

11 - Gloomhaven Square A

Too many AI decisions to make, we really needed the app to help track everything. 

Got to the boss and nabbed the treasure chest after running past everyone and letting our allies do the work.

Sadly we were all exhausted before doing even half the damage needed to beat the boss. Plus we were all drunk and tired by then. #bgstats
A win on Basic Building Side A medium (8 rounds) #bgstats
A close loss (Basic Side A - Medium 8 rounds) #bgstats
Another loss (not even close this time) as Basic Side A Medium 8 Rounds #bgstats

First trial solo game (basic building, no expansions). 

Made a mistake during setup with the project cards but only noticed halfway through when I kept not being able to use my dice ? Turns out there are six FIXED project cards (1-6) and I shouldn't have assumed they should be shuffled.

Got the main gameplay quickly enough but just couldn't get the last building stage before running out of time. Reset, try again! #bgstats

Setup for second attempt, then realised the fixed 1-6 project cards (which included the two cards where you have to move your engineer two spaces) meant that I had to think more carefully about which cards to use. 

Found the beautiful "hook" to this puzzle as well. Each turn could be brilliant - using both dice for maximum effect - but you need a little luck and some forward planning to make that happen.

Ended up completing the final building stage using the project card to complete with a couple of turns spare! Will go for a harder difficulty/other building card for my next game! #bgstats

play.comments:
Brought out Pandemic as our first post-lockdown cooperative experience. Showed my mum the game, although she played Thunderbirds with us before so she grasped it quickly.

We had disastrous luck as red disease ran out of control in 2 epidemics and we ran out of cubes very swiftly :-(

We set it back up to try again!

Got the game set back up and had a much better time. We were able to keep all the diseases under control and even eradicated several along the way. 

Enjoyed seeing my mum take turns for herself properly, not even asking us what she should do but knowing the most efficient way to use her character to beat the bad cubes!

#bgstats
I won as I got the pot fullest in the last round! #bgstats

Introduced my mum to Carcassonne, she loved it instantly! 

She enjoyed the tile-laying and although she had a little difficulty with some of the scoring it was a successful introduction!

#bgstats

A head-melting introductory game which admittedly felt more of a struggle than most. Too many phases, turns, icons on the various cards and tracks to smoothly enjoy the first game... plus the crunch between deck- and dice-drafting left my head spinning as I tried to work out what to use my dice for. No idea who was winning but Naomi upgraded more so stole the victory! #bgstats

@attributes.name: Clank! In! Space!: A Deck-Building Adventure

@attributes.name: Clank! In! Space!: A Deck-Building Adventure

play.comments: No pics but had Promenade, Doomsday Cannon and Hydroponics. Close game until the end but I managed to sneak out and killed Naomi in my first escaped boss attack turn. She was in the Cargo Bay so still a partial victory but I took it on points overall! #bgstats

@attributes.name: The Lord of the Rings: Journeys in Middle-Earth

play.comments: First campaign mission for Bones of Arnor, solo game with two characters to learn the rules. Beravor as Pathfinder and Elena as Musician. Found many things confusing which slowed the whole process down but managed to get there in the end. Still unclear what the app will track really. Lost the mission but gained 3xp. #bgstats

@attributes.name: Clank! In! Space!: A Deck-Building Adventure

play.comments: A tough but enjoyable game where we were hammered by clank and boss advancement early on (there are at least 3 archive tokens!?!). Managed to both get into the Command module but were killed within a turn of each other so we both lost! #bgstats

Big scoring round, some good fortune cards and lucky draws - my final round got me all the way to the pot handle for the first time... but Naomi had already stormed ahead on points so took the win! #bgstats

@attributes.name: Clank! In! Space!: A Deck-Building Adventure

play.comments: Standard setup again - trickier from the start for both of us. Fairly even damage but some unfortunate clank and lots of boss attacks. We had each just collected our artifacts when we were knocked out (Naomi first, I had one turn before her boss attack killed me too!) #bgstats

@attributes.name: Clank! In! Space!: A Deck-Building Adventure

play.comments: Standard first-game 2p setup with Hydroponics, Med Bay and Doomsday Cannon. I was close to being killed for most of the game but managed to speed through the escape to make it out with 1 HP left. Naomi still won on points and was first to escape (1 turn before me) and a full health bar! #bgstats
A close but low-scoring game. Several explosions and loads of whites right from the first draw! #bgstats
A fun game, my risk-averse strategy paid off (only 1 explosion over the 9 turns) where Naomi had 4. Loved it, perhaps feeds the gambler in Naomi a bit too much though ? #bgstats

@attributes.name: Choose Your Own Adventure: House of Danger

play.comments: Played through the first chapter, went back to explore a few areas. Died twice (shiny object and violin player) but was worth it! Managed to find (we think) most of the psychic objects, 1 premonition, and finished with a Psychic Level of 10 and a Danger Level of 5. #bgstats

Played the free Print-and-Play case made available during Covid-19. Managed to solve the case (90/100) but were slightly confused by some of the extra information presented in the case, but not actually used. This appears to be part of the following chapters of the case, which we cannot solve without further resources (require the base game). Still enjoyable and we managed to get through it pretty well. #bgstats

Beat the Archpriestess quickly which prevented any serious ritual cards for the second phase - the Daemon. 

Finished it with plenty of health spare, was perhaps a little easy by the end! That ended the campaign, now just need to get The Lost Village to finish off the story! #bgstats

Beat the bastard! A good bunch of damage-dealing cards, plus with one of Naomi's "discard a card" abilities we managed to get the master to discard the "Escape" card which would have ended the game! Lucky draw but good game - and we get to level up now! #bgstats
Got a lucky deal with the cards and ended up romping through it. Master didn't stand a chance. #bgstats
Got totally stomped from the beginning (chapter 2, human zealot). Not even close and could not get any momentum going. We lost... so badly. Master escaped after around 10 turns. #bgstats
Realised we did the exits wrong! Faint PnP printing meant I missed the specific road or rail exits! Probably didn't change the score too much and learned for next time! #bgstats

Encounter 1 - beginner difficulty. 

Got the master down to 3 health but could not finish him off. Devastating continual stunning of champions. So damn hard ? #bgstats
Tie decided by food (3-2 to Matt) #bgstats
Absolutely smashed. Naomi ended with more health than she started. I completely struggled the whole way. Stupid Wizard cat. #bgstats

First game learning the rules. Nice and easy to pick up, had to check for clarification when the Ambassador came out on the board. I went for a heavy building strategy which was moderately successful while Naomi blasted through as many quests as possible. Ended up with 5 points difference - so tight!  #bgstats

First game, learning as we go. Nice and simple deckbuilder with a couple of neat twists to give depth (ally, champion). Only criticism so far is the combat pool could do with tokens to keep track when you get a combo going. #bgstats
Online game where it was close-fought but ended up with a boost on VP at the end. Good evening's gaming and unsure how it would play out even during the last generation. #bgstats
First tied game! Decided by unused food tokens - 6 to me, 4 for Naomi. Close fought game and quite even throughout, only a few expansion birds and bonus cards but still a solid game. #bgstats
Some very dodgy scoring going on. Me and Oliver were about 10 points ahead until we went outside for a smoke, then somehow seemed to lose immediately - so, er, apparently the girls won! #bgstats

Finished the Easy Game mode. Same roles as our tutorial game, with Naomi jumping into the Commander role when she got back from work. Was tense and some dramatic failed rolls added even more doom to the mix but we managed to smash the final mission in a couple of rounds. Really good fun, will be coming back to try "real time" on a higher difficulty level soon. #bgstats

@attributes.name: Adventure Time Card Wars: Finn vs. Jake

play.comments: Instant devastation! Was fairly even until 1 used a couple of abilities which let me draw lots of cards (9 in hand). Naomi then played a spell "deal 1 damage to your opponent for each card in their hand" which smashed me into the ground. End score - Naomi 10/25HP, me with 0/25HP. #bgstats

@attributes.name: Adventure Time Card Wars: Finn vs. Jake

play.comments: Did no damage to Naomi whatsoever. I need to get better at this game. #bgstats

@attributes.name: Adventure Time Card Wars: Finn vs. Jake

play.comments: A closer battle this time but Naomi still had me on the rocks. I finally managed to draw The Pig (and then Floop The Pig), which I used to undermine her cornfield-reliant strategy... but it wasn't enough. End HP - Naomi 17, Me 0. #bgstats

@attributes.name: Adventure Time Card Wars: Finn vs. Jake

play.comments: Drew 4 creatures out of 20 cards through the game. Loads of magic and buildings which didn't help to stop the destruction. Naomi took 8 damage in the time I took 25. #bgstats

Digital game on mobile/Steam where we sped through in an evening. Was a fun game, a lot of the "take that" cards were used and we ended up with a face across the surface in the battle of bush and city. Rich one point behind Naomi, with me and Loz a way off in the final tally. #bgstats

A slightly failed attempt to play using *only* the new bird and bonus cards, plus only the new round goals. I absolutely loved the new bonus cards but couldn't make them work with the limited selection of birds available. Naomi had fun with some new combo powers on bird cards and romped home to the victory. Have mixed all the cards in now so we can play properly next time! #bgstats

First attempt at the tutorial mission, which we had to leave incomplete as it took so damn long to get into it! Probably a 4-5 hour session, most of that trying to grasp our roles and the gameplay flow. Ended on phase/round 3 or 4 (around half way we guessed).

Even when the app is streamlined and well-designed, you can't go wrong with a rules reference book so we can clarify rules and check we're on the right track. 

Naomi arrived after phase/round 1 and played Commander (budget + interceptors). Oliver was Central Officer (app + satellites). Amber was Chief Scientist (research). I played as Squad Leader (mission + base defence). #bgstats

play.comments: Short evening game with not much in terms of big points but a few good combos which helped me win but it was still close! #bgstats
Quick but low-scoring game, both struggled with playing birds and getting many round/bonus points here. #bgstats
Another low-scoring game, better bonus/round points but still no huge scores #bgstats

Played the "easy" board with 2 players, first game for me. We had a hard time early on with L1 encounters (3 enemies) but found the L2 encounters easy. Farmed those a little, then with our last 2 bonfires we took on the mini-boss which we blitzed, then we went straight into the final boss. Was pretty easy by that point, but it was still fun seeing the boss mechanics and getting lucky with the deck. Very fun game, want to play again on hard mode! #bgstats

Showed Amber and Oliver TM. They got it quickly and ended up winning with great production and milestone/awards. Oliver was very happy. I came in 4th place with 58 points... then found an event card I hadn't counted with -2VP on it. I died a little inside. #bgstats

Me as the Hood vs. Naomi and Oliver as Thunderbirds, with extra expansion stuff from Above and Beyond, Tracy Island (chars and vehicles). Close at the beginning and almost too hard for the 'birds to beat Act 2 with the number of vehicles required but it balanced towards the end and after a gruelling battle they smashed Act 3 to save the world! #bgstats

First game of Wingspan for Amber and Oliver. Picked up quickly and ended up with really close-run scoring. Naomi "did a Little Tom" and left during Round 4, leaving us instructions for her final 4 actions. She came last sadly. Oliver stormed it with 3 completed bonuses and Amber a close 2nd with 26 eggs laid! #bgstats

Naomi as UMNI and me as Helion. All went very well for me but Naomi struggled to keep up. She felt quite ill in fairness and I got lucky with initial cards. Hoped to break 200 but no luck. Did manage to get the Capital surrounded by oceans which was fun. #bgstats

One of the tightest games we've played. Both playing to new strategies - Naomi as Eco Corp with loads of microbes/animals on cards. Me as Jovian bonus with loads of cash production which I spent on cities and expensive event cards. Ended up with 20 points separating us after 3 hours of play! #bgstats
Naomi quite ill which is the reason she wasn't quite on form. #bgstats
Both had a hard time with bonus and round goals, most of the points were bird points and eggs. #bgstats

A tight game with both of us playing to our strengths (Me - cities, Naomi - energy). I ended up smashing the VP on greenery for the cities too which won the game. First game using custom player boards too! #bgstats
First game, just getting to hang of the general gameplay and actions - not to mention the character special abilities! #bgstats
2nd game - mostly the same as the first to get used to it. #bgstats
3 final game - Amber ducked out as she'd had too many Mojitos.  #bgstats
Played a few games of Dominion with the base game. Tried all the cards from the shop/market through the games. #bgstats

Absolutely smashed by Rich, he took us to the cleaners! We were pretty tired by that point so weren't paying enough attention and he photographed and conspired to steal the game in half an hour! #bgstats
I won the first game by a few points but it was close. Came down to puddings! #bgstats
Think Mia won the second game - good variety and a wasabi that pushed her over the line. #bgstats

First real time playthrough of Sonar - with Rich, Miles and Naomi on one team, and Tom, Lindsay, Loz and me on the other. Intense as hell (alpha map) and Rich/Miles coordinated moves in quick succession, along with "safe movement patterns" meant we were utterly outplayed ? #bgstats
Showed Wingspan to mum and Jake. Took a couple of rounds for things to make sense, and I think my mum struggled right up to the end.  #bgstats

Think this game was won by bonus points, the egg laying strategy didn't work well on this game!

This game was finished by Little Tom writing his last 5 actions (Round 4) on a piece of paper and leaving in a rush! #bgstats

Introduced Rich (later replaced by Tom) and Lindsay to the game. Good mix of races and powers - lots of debate over the "reinforcement die rolled on each conquest" power, eventually resolved through a re-reading of the manual. #bgstats
First campaign of Imperial Assault. Rebels won two story missions and Empire won one. Lost Han Solo to a failed play, but held Vader off during his scenario by one action for the win. #bgstats
Few rounds of The Chameleon, hard to get the hang of (knowing the level of detail/fakery in your clues takes a little time) but enjoyable game overall! #bgstats

A treacherous first game, slightly baffled by all the rules but sorta managed to get the hang of it all by the end. Weirdly, Oliver (who knew the game and was teaching us the rules) managed to win it. #bgstats

Tried out the Tools of Hero Kind (Items) expansion - and it was a bit confusing. It added another level of strategy to the game but at the expense of some slowed rounds and head-scratching moments where the boss abilities of the items didn't seem to make sense. The items didn't make a major difference to the end score - Naomi romped home before I had a chance to even get half the souls I needed!
A Sunday evening of Wingspan fun - and I thought that I had lost this one with some terrible bonus cards - however even Naomi's 3 bonus cards weren't enough to take the win off me this time!

A final game of Wingspan for the evening - we fought hard but I just went all-in with eggs (ended with 19 eggs!). That was largely due to the bonus card of "birds with at least 4 eggs on them" which was tricky to get any points out of! However, it was enough to claim the win - I think I'm actually getting the hang of this now! Naomi claims her losses this evening were due to illness - any excuse! :-p

Tried the solo variant of Wingspan (Automa) while watching the live general election debate. Quite confusing, had to pay a lot of attention to keep track of the round order and actions for the automa (even with cubes and reference cards). Ended up winning significantly - but I was playing on the "Easy" mode. Will try again on medium or hard when I get chance and see how I get on!
Another late night game of Wingspan - this time closer than ever! We had an even spread of round points but Naomi managed to swing it with bonus and egg points - so close!

First learning game of Captain Sonar - played turn by turn as it was just the 2 of us. I completely lost Naomi when she went silent and didn't managed to pick her up again until it was too late. Complete domination - she took no damage and I was smashed!

Showed Amber and Oliver the game while at the pub. We had a good introductory game while eating loaded chips - great fun - and it came down to the wire in the end. Only 4 points between the lowest and highest scores!

Another day, another lost game at Small World :-p

Naomi picked wisely with the Alchemist Elves, which seemed impossible to wipe off the map (how to you force that race into decline!?!) and I went through the Spirit Amazons and the Dragon Master Ratmen - still not able to take her down enough to win the game!

First game of Wingspan - was really just learning the rules. Not many "chained combos" or anything especially exciting came up - but we enjoyed getting to grips with it! Even when learning it only took us around 60 mins to finish - pleasingly quick! Naomi wiped the floor with me though - mainly on bird points and completed bonus cards!

Second game of Wingspan - loads more chained combos and "between turns" actions coming up! Got a bit more into the strategy of it... although I still lost by the exact same margin! Couldn't complete my bonus card for full points (have birds with eggs) and Naomi had 2 birds which had "between your turns" actions which gained eggs each time I used that action anyway! Dammit!

Third game of Wingspan (still "friendly") but got the hang of it now so was able to quickly speed through the rounds. Naomi was better on both the round and bonus points, but I had a better selection of birds and 10 eggs which took the win

Fourth game of Wingspan - to round off the evening (4 games in one day!). We had hardly any "between rounds" bonuses but I completely fudged the bonus and round goals, leading to my downfall! It was a much tighter game overall though!

First game - got the rules slightly wrong but not sure it would have made a difference. Naomi's Alchemist Sorcerers absolutely stormed through the entire game. I managed to get through 3 different races (Berzerker Giants, Wealthy Orcs, Stout Ratmen) but was always on the back foot!
First attempts at Sushi Roll, not having a friggin clue what each of the ingredients were and how points worked. The damn Maki Rolls, puddings and menu/chopstick tokens were the decider.
Second attempt - knew a bit better what was going on but she still beat me.... FFS.

Played a standard game of Boss Monster to introduce Amber and Oliver to the game. Was a close-run game up until the end. Naomi was first to die (after we totally dicked her over and made her take 4 wounds in a single turn) and Amber went soon after. Was down to me and Oliver - he almost had me but I managed to freeze one of his rooms when he could deal _just_ enough damage to beat the epic heroes he'd taken and ended up dying, so I won by default!

First game with Amber and Oliver of Thunderbirds. Picked it up nice and quick - we were on top of the disasters and schemes right from the word "go". Think we were slightly lucky with the lack of space disasters throughout. Played on the easy (I, II, III) difficulty.

@attributes.name: Boss Monster: The Dungeon Building Card Game

play.comments:
Another quick game of Boss Monster to wrap up the night. We had a good battle - each taking 3 or 4 initial heroes and a couple of wounds - but it looked like Loz would whoop our asses.

Fortunately, we had the spells ready to totally dick him over in the final few rounds and he was knocked out. My middling dungeon setup managed to take the final 2 epic fighters for the win!

Played Year 1, then Year 3 and Year 6 as an introduction.

We blitzed the early years (obviously) and played well as a team, then decided to speed up Year 6 (and guarantee victory) with a small cheat to the initial hand setup.

Wouldn't recommend it, but it made Year 6 pass quickly enough that we could go to bed at a reasonable hour!

@attributes.name: Boss Monster: The Dungeon Building Card Game

play.comments:
Played a quick round of Boss Monster, without expansions.

Was a quick game, Loz took the win in the end with a nice run of defeated heroes (even though we tried to hit him with spells).

Picking up where we left off last time, we blasted through Year 7 and the bloody Horcruxes (using the triple Voldemort variant).

After a few failed attempts - losing the first location within a few rounds and accepting defeat - we managed to get a bit of momentum going.

The successful playthrough was an absolute breeze - making the most of our abilities/proficiencies and getting some really good Hogwarts card combos going (Elder Wand plus Accios, anyone?).

We smashed through the penultimate and final Voldemort with one punishing blast - 46 damage in a single turn! Thanks to Rich and his deck-building prowess for that absolute domination! Happy faces all round :-D

Played a couple of games of Thunderbirds this evening but will log the plays separately - firstly this one - a vanilla game to show Lindsay the rules/general gameplay. 

The game went well, and we managed to foil the Hood with only minimal peril in the early stages (we were two Hood advances away from death but pulled it back. Playing on the easy setting though - not too much trouble for any of us!

Played a 1v4 game of Thunderbirds with all 3 expansions - and Rich played as the Hood. 

It was a new experience for all the Thunderbirds - plus we had NONE of the Tracy brothers as characters so we were at a disadvantage for most of the Rescues. 

We all had to learn what exactly the Hood was up to - and how best to counter his dastardly schemes - but sadly in the end we miscalculated how long we had to defeat a disaster and it hit the end of the track. 

The Thunderbirds lost and the Hood cackled with glee :'-( #bgstats

Lindsay's first game of TM - we took it slow with the rules explanation and general flow of the game so we could talk strategies and gameplay in more detail.

Me, Naomi and Rich took non-beginner Corporations but none of us actually played to our strengths very well.

After around 4 hours of play, we wrapped up with no idea who had taken the win - it was Lindsay! Beginner's luck I guess! :-)

@attributes.location: Rental Cottage, St. Johns, Isle of Man

play.comments: Game played over several evenings on holiday. #bgstats

Epic 2-player session where we managed to get both space bases, the Capital City and Noctis City on the board! 

After many, many generations of developing Mars - to the point where we nearly ran out of cubes and spaces to develop on - we ended the game. 

* Final Scores *
Naomi - 148
Matt - 133 #bgstats

Played Year 1 to introduce Louis and Jordan to the rules, which was obviously a walk in the park. Then tried to jump straight to Year 4, which went badly.... twice. Really bad luck with the cards - combinations of Lucius Malfoy and the Basilisk were absolutely crushing us - so we never actually made it past Year 4. Still thoroughly enjoyed it! #bgstats

Quick game - the first for Jordan and Louis - where we briefly introduced the rules. The picked it up quickly and had fun speeding the vehicles around the globe to thwart The Hood's schemes. Played on easy difficulty (Scheme I, II, III) and managed to beat the final scheme without much difficulty! #bgstats
